solution: ```cpp
class Solution {
public:
    string removeOccurrences(string s, string part) {
        if (part.empty()) return s;
        size_t pos;
        while ((pos = s.find(part)) != string::npos) {
            s.erase(pos, part.size());
        }
        return s;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n * m * k) where n = s.length, m = part.length, k = number of removals (worst-case O(n/m))
space complexity: O(1) auxiliary (in-place modification)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Repeatedly find and erase the leftmost occurrence of part in s until none remain. Uses built-in string operations for simplicity and clarity; worst-case quadratic but fast in practice due to small constraints and optimized STL.

